						<summary>

						<p>The record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1077, Bhāva,</hi> the <hi rend="bold">month Dhanus</hi> and <hi rend="bold">Saṅkrmaṇa.</hi> The inscription belongs to the reign of the Āḷupa king <hi rend="bold">Kaviyāḷupēndra.</hi> A certain <hi rend="bold">Maunayōgi</hi> is stated to have granted some land for the service of the god Nakharēśvara of <hi rend="bold">Basurepura.</hi></p>						

